<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>My opinion.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Darknyss">Darknyss</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:54 p.m. 25/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> My opinion.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2090" TARGET=_self>Pk balancing for wizard types</A> (Ghouldan)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I agree with you completely, wizards have NOTHING to lose when they pk and everything to gain (I've never heard of looting spellbooks, how do you do that?). And more often then not, they will win and gain something that took hours, to weeks, or maybe even a month or more to earn in less than a minute or less. And if they start to lose, even if they don't use gate or shadowstep or something like that, they can always turn tail and run. Melee classes don't very well have this option, with wizard spells being long range, and pets chasing you all the way into cities until you zone. And you didn't even bring up the topic of root. I know at high levels root isn't a big things, but at low levels, root dominates everything, it can't be beaten. Sure, I always hear people saying GET A BOW, but the people saying this are the wizards usually, and have never really compared. 20 damage from a bow, if it's a really good bow (low level speaking here). How does this compare to 80 or more? And the channeling skill, at high levels, lets you sit and cast your spells while being pounded on without losing concentration, that should be toned down. I agree with putting in a true autoattack function, but don't make it as good as NPC's, that would shift the power all the way to melee classes, but there should be an autochasing function so they can't just hold control and jump around and cast a spell whenever your packet loss makes them warp. Maybe make it so you can either have autochasing or autoattack on, but not BOTH. That would be fair, IMO. If more people would post suggestions, you could probably find something better, and then we could all petition or feedback about it. They've listened before, if we all do this, they'll listen again, and I for one am sick of having little chance against a wizard, even if I am better than them (That's not boasting, I know there are people that SHOULD be able to beat me, but any idiot can win if they play a wizard.)

<P>Darknyss
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
